arrow.name: arrow
arrow.desc: A finely shaped wooden rod with a sharp metal tip.  Can be equipped to the Ammo slot via the Inventory > Equipment screen.  This type of ammo is used with Bows.

bolt.name: bolt
bolt.desc: A sharpened metal rod. Can be equipped to the Ammo slot via the Inventory > Equipment screen.  This type of ammo is used with Crossbows.

empty-potion-bottle.name: empty potion bottle
empty-potion-bottle.desc: A small flask carved from gemstones.  Used to make potions with the Alchemy skill.

guild-color.name: guild color
guild-color.desc:
Equip this item via the Inventory > Equipment screen to gain buffs to hitpoints and maxhitpoints. In addition, using this item from inventory will set your guild color.
    Meaning, it will turn your characters name to your guilds color.

the-egg-of-time.name: The Egg of Time
the-egg-of-time.desc: This strange egg ticks methodically as if it was a watch, which begs the question what gives birth to a ticking egg.

the-cookie-of-life.name: The Cookie of Life
the-cookie-of-life.desc: This cookie was said to have fallen to Myzan many millions of years ago, it brought with it the seeds of life.

the-sword-of-death.name: The Sword of Death
the-sword-of-death.desc: This sword is said to bring death to whoever touches it, the records arent clear if this is intended as a metaphor for bloodshed caused by the sword or if merely touching the sword kills you.

the-gem-of-twelve-dimensions.name: The Gem of Twelve Dimensions
the-gem-of-twelve-dimensions.desc: This gem is said to offer insights into parallel realities that overlap our own.

the-book-of-all-knowledge.name: The Book of all Knowledge
the-book-of-all-knowledge.desc: This book is said to hold the knowledge of the universe, only no one can figure out how to open it.

the-harp-of-romance.name: The Harp of Romance
the-harp-of-romance.desc: This harp is said to make anyone that uses it irresistable to the opposite sex, unfortunately all the strings are broken.

barrendown-legend-tablet.name: Barrendown Legend Tablet
barrendown-legend-tablet.desc: This tablet was created to honor Elvric Barrendown a gnomish Bard who helped recover Godric`s Horn for the Dwarves.

cragstone-legend-tablet.name: Cragstone Legend Tablet
cragstone-legend-tablet.desc: This tablet was created to honor Meribeth Cragstone a gnomish Berserker who helped recover Godric`s Horn for the Dwarves.

freebreeze-legend-tablet.name: Freebreeze Legend Tablet
freebreeze-legend-tablet.desc: This tablet was created to honor Alexia Freebreeze a centaur Wizard who helped the gnomes recover Liliden`s Song.

frostvale-legend-tablet.name: Frostvale Legend Tablet
frostvale-legend-tablet.desc: This table was created to honor Nerik Frostvale a human Cleric who helped rediscover Imerin`s Glade for the Elves.

grimbrow-legend-tablet.name: Grimbrow Legend Tablet
grimbrow-legend-tablet.desc: This table was created to honor Gaedrin Grimbrow a dwarven Soldier who helped the Humans discover the End of the World.

greater-armor-patch.name: Greater armor patch
greater-armor-patch.desc:
Increases a ARMOR bonus on an item by 10% when fitted.

Only one patch per item can be fitted at any one time, patches can be removed if needed.

bolt-tip.name: bolt tip
bolt-tip.desc: This bolt tip is used to make arrows.

arrowhead.name: arrowhead
arrowhead.desc: This arrowhead is used to make arrows.

longtooth-legend-tablet.name: Longtooth Legend Tablet
longtooth-legend-tablet.desc: This tablet was created to honor Laretta Longtooth a centaur Ranger who helped the Gnomes recover Liliden`s Song.

proudline-legend-tablet.name: Proudline Legend Tablet
proudline-legend-tablet.desc: This table was created to honor Mandor Proudline a human Veteran who helped rediscover Imerin`s Glade for the Elves.

armor-patch.name: Armor patch
armor-patch.desc:
Increases a ARMOR bonus on an item by 5% when fitted.

Only one patch per item can be fitted at any one time, patches can be removed if needed.

pureheart-legend-tablet.name: Pureheart Legend Tablet
pureheart-legend-tablet.desc: This table was created to honor Jaene Pureheart a elvish Paladin who helped the Centaurs recover Mernia`s Stave.

silverclaw-legend-tablet.name: Silverclaw Legend Tablet
silverclaw-legend-tablet.desc: This table was created to honor Heather Silverclaw a dwarven Thief who helped the Humans discover the End of the World.

strongmoon-legend-tablet.name: Strongmoon Legend Tablet
strongmoon-legend-tablet.desc: This table was created to honor Stiven Strongmoon a elvish Druid who helped the Centaurs recover Mernia`s Stave.

dart-tip.name: dart tip
dart-tip.desc: This dart tip is used to make darts

light-yellow-potion.name: light yellow potion
light-yellow-potion.desc: This potion can be used to cure stamina in combat.

yellow-potion.name: yellow potion
yellow-potion.desc: This potion can be used to cure stamina in combat.

dark-yellow-potion.name: dark yellow potion
dark-yellow-potion.desc: This potion can be used to cure stamina in combat.

light-grey-potion.name: light grey potion
light-grey-potion.desc: This potion can be used to cure disease in combat.

grey-potion.name: grey potion
grey-potion.desc: This potion can be used to cure poison in combat.

dark-grey-potion.name: dark grey potion
dark-grey-potion.desc: This potion can be used to cure both poison and disease in combat.

armor-strengthener.name: Armor strengthener
armor-strengthener.desc:
Increases a ARMOR bonus on an item by 4% when fitted.

Only one patch per item can be fitted at any one time, patches can be removed if needed.

smoothstone.name: smoothstone
smoothstone.desc: A smoothly polished rock.  Can be equipped in the Ammo slot via the Inventory > Equipment screen.  Used as ammo for Slings.

bullet.name: bullet
bullet.desc: A pointed bit of metal with an explosive charge.  Can be equipped to the Ammo slot via the Inventory > Equipment screen.  Used as ammo for Guns.

stone.name: stone
stone.desc: A large, heavy rounded rock.  Can be equipped to the Ammo slot via the Inventory > Equipment screen.  Used as ammo for Catapults.

flaming-potion.name: flaming potion
flaming-potion.desc:
A vial filled with explosive contents. Can be equipped
    to the Ammo slot via the Inventory > Equipment screen. Can be used as ammo for scoops (Thrown Magic).

shocking-potion.name: shocking potion
shocking-potion.desc: Lightning in a bottle!  Can be equipped to the Ammo slot via the Inventory > Equipment screen.  Used as ammo for Scoops.

earthen-potion.name: earthen potion
earthen-potion.desc: This potion is used as ammunition for scoops.

poisoning-potion.name: poisoning potion
poisoning-potion.desc: This potion is used as ammunition for scoops.

lesser-armor-patch.name: Lesser armor patch
lesser-armor-patch.desc:
Increases a ARMOR bonus on an item by 2% when fitted.

Only one patch per item can be fitted at any one time, patches can be removed if needed.

champion-goggles.name: Champion goggles
champion-goggles.desc: This item is a reward for gaining enough fame in your faction.

spiked-shoulder-pads.name: spiked shoulder pads
spiked-shoulder-pads.desc: These shoulder pads, with spikes attached, are made to intimidate. Just make sure not to shrug. Equip this item via the Inventory > Equipment screen. In addition if it has a spell on it you can activate the spell via the Inventory  > Spells screen after you have equipped it.

quaking-arrow.name: quaking arrow
quaking-arrow.desc: An arrow imbued with the powers of earth. Can be equipped to the Ammo slot via the Inventory > Equipment screen. Used as ammo for Bows.

thermal-arrow.name: thermal arrow
thermal-arrow.desc: An arrow that feels hot under your fingers. Can be equipped to the Ammo slot via the Inventory > Equipment screen. Used as ammo for Bows.

skull-of-corruption.name: Skull of Corruption
skull-of-corruption.desc:
A skull of dark magicks. Can be equipped to Bonus 1 or Bonus 2 slots via the Inventory > Equipment screen. This is a bought extra item and it can be bought via the File > Buy Extras > Amazing Items screen.

    Use the Inventory > Spells screen after equipping this item to possess pets using the Corrupt Soul spell it contains (Unlimited Charges).

stout-armor-patch.name: Stout armor patch
stout-armor-patch.desc:
Increases a ARMOR bonus on an item by 15% when fitted.

Only one patch per item can be fitted at any one time, patches can be removed if needed.

bullet-mold.name: bullet mold
bullet-mold.desc: This bullet mold is used to make bullets.

dark-star.name: Dark Star
dark-star.desc: The Dark star is a strange weapon,dark energies eminate from it granting it's wielder the power of darkness. It requires no weapon skill to wield and thus styles can't be used. It gives bonuses to Attack power which boosts melee damage, Mana which allows you to cast more spells inside and outside of combat and gives a Boost to the Dark magic skill.

skull-of-vampirism.name: Skull of Vampirism
skull-of-vampirism.desc: A treasured creation of the Vampire race. Can be equipped to the Bonus 1 or Bonus 2 slots via the Inventory > Equipment screen. This item can be gained from scratch cards.

awakening-potion.name: awakening potion
awakening-potion.desc: This potion can be used as a defensive item in combat to reduce the effects of paralysation based on the material level of the potion.

neutralising-potion.name: neutralising potion
neutralising-potion.desc: This potion can be used as a defensive item in combat to reduce the effects of nulification based on the material level of the potion.

lock.name: lock
lock.desc: This lock can be fitted into a room to lock the room.

lesser-fury-patch.name: Lesser fury patch
lesser-fury-patch.desc:
Increases a ATTACK POWER bonus on an item by 10% when fitted.

Only one patch per item can be fitted at any one time, patches can be removed if needed.

fury-patch.name: Fury patch
fury-patch.desc:
Increases a ATTACK POWER bonus on an item by 15% when fitted.

Only one patch per item can be fitted at any one time, patches can be removed if needed.

greater-fury-patch.name: Greater fury patch
greater-fury-patch.desc:
Increases a ATTACK POWER bonus on an item by 20% when fitted.

Only one patch per item can be fitted at any one time, patches can be removed if needed.

magnificent-fury-patch.name: Magnificent fury patch
magnificent-fury-patch.desc:
Increases a ATTACK POWER bonus on an item by 35% when fitted.

Only one patch per item can be fitted at any one time, patches can be removed if needed.

tinkers-lock.name: tinkers lock
tinkers-lock.desc: This lock can be fitted into an item to lock the item.

small-blade-hilt.desc: This hilt is used in the construction of bladed items such as Daggers.

This item is a gift from Guide Derwa for completing one of the first quests on the estate.

    This item can be equipped to the Bonus slot to provide a bonus to your health, furthermore you can use the Inventory > Spells screen to activate a secondary effect on this item that will provide you with additional health.

eye-of-the-first.name: Eye of the First
eye-of-the-first.desc: A Reaper only item, it is given to you by Velric Bloodhorn for gathering the remnants of The First. This item has no armor requirement and thus anyone may equip it. It gives a bonus to Stamina which gives a passive boost to Hit Points and allows you to do more damage via styles as well as Intelligence which boosts the damage of most spells and increases the amount of mana you have to cast with.

dagger.name: dagger
dagger.desc: A simple short range weapon that can be used by almost all professions. It can be made from any level material, and can be equiped via the Inventory > Equipment screen. In addition if it has a spell on it you can activate the spell via the Inventory > Spells screen after you have equipped it.

legendary-dagger.name: Legendary dagger
legendary-dagger.desc: A Legendary dagger, It requires the DAGGERS skill to equip. It gives bonuses to Attack power which raises melee damage, Speed which improves your chances to dodge magical attacks, and Stamina which allows you to do more damage via styles as well as raise your Hit Points.

legendary-skewer.name: Legendary skewer
legendary-skewer.desc: A Legendary dagger, It requires the DAGGERS skill to equip. It gives bonuses to Attack power and Strength which raises melee damage as well as Stamina which allows you to do more damage via styles as well as raise your Hit Points.

legendary-dirk.name: Legendary dirk
legendary-dirk.desc: A Legendary dagger, It requires the DAGGERS skill to equip. It gives bonuses to Attack power which raises melee damage, Dexterity which improves your chances to dodge melee attacks, and Stamina which allows you to do more damage via styles as well as raise your Hit Points.

riftblade.name: Riftblade
riftblade.desc: This weapon gives attack power which boosts melee damage, It may be equipped by anyone with the SWORDS skill.

short-legendary-sword.name: Short Legendary sword
short-legendary-sword.desc: A Legendary sword, It requires the SWORDS skill to equip. It gives bonuses to Attack power which raises melee damage, Stamina which gives a passive boost to Hit Points as well as allowing you to cause more damage via styles and Speed which helps you dodge Magic attacks.

long-legendary-sword.name: Long Legendary sword
long-legendary-sword.desc: A Legendary sword, It requires the SWORDS skill to equip. It gives bonuses to Attack power which raises melee damage and Stamina which gives a passive boost to Hit Points as well as allowing you to cause more damage via styles and Dexterity which helps you dodge melee attacks.

battle-axe.name: battle axe
battle-axe.desc: A battle axe, weapon of choice of Dwarves everywhere. This Weapon requires the TWO-HANDED AXES skill to equip. It gives a bonus to Attack Power which allows you to deal extra melee damage.

legendary-hatchet.name: Legendary hatchet
legendary-hatchet.desc: A Legendary axe, It requires the AXES skill to equip. It gives bonuses to Attack power which raises melee damage as well as Dexterity and Speed which will aid you in dodging melee and magic attacks, Respectfully.

legendary-axe.name: Legendary axe
legendary-axe.desc: A Legendary axe, It requires the AXES skill to equip. It gives bonuses to Attack power which raises melee damage, Stamina which gives a passive boost to Hit Points as well as allowing you to do more damage via styles. It also gives a bonus to the Frenzy skill which while in battle will allow you to gain rage points which will in turn allow you to cause extra damage to your opponent.

legendary-half-axe.name: Legendary half axe
legendary-half-axe.desc: A Legendary axe, It requires the AXES skill to equip. It gives bonuses to Attack power and Strength which raises melee damage as well as Stamina which gives a passive boost to Hit Points as well as allowing you to do more damage via styles.

legendary-staff.name: Legendary staff
legendary-staff.desc: A Legendary Staff, It requires the STAVES skill to equip. It gives bonuses to Attack power and Strength which raises melee damage as well as Stamina which gives a passive boost to Hit Points as well as allowing you to do more damage via styles.

legendary-quarterstaff.name: Legendary quarterstaff
legendary-quarterstaff.desc: A Legendary staff, It requires the STAVES skill to equip. It gives bonuses to Attack power which raises melee damage, Dexterity which aids you in dodging melee attacks, and Stamina which gives a passive boost to Hit Points as well as allowing you to do more damage via styles.

short-legendary-staff.name: Short Legendary staff
short-legendary-staff.desc: A Legendary staff, It requires the STAVES skill to equip. It gives bonuses to Attack power which raises melee damage, Intelligence which gives a passive boost to Mana as well as raising the damage of most spells and Mana which allows you to cast more spells inside and outside of combat.

legendary-mace.name: Legendary mace
legendary-mace.desc: A Legendary Cudgel, It requires the MACES skill to equip. It gives bonuses to Attack power and Strength which raises melee damage as well as Stamina which gives a passive boost to Hit Points as well as allowing you to do more damage via styles.

large-legendary-shield.name: Large Legendary shield
large-legendary-shield.desc: A Legendary Shield, It Requires the TWO-HANDED SHIELD skill to Equip. It gives bonuses to Attack power and Strength which boosts melee damage as well as Armor which will lessen melee Damage. Shields give the added effect of randomly lessening melee damage you recieve, the amount removed is between 1 and the total DPR the weapon has.

legendary-heater-shield.name: Legendary heater shield
legendary-heater-shield.desc: A Legendary Shield, It Requires the TWO-HANDED SHIELD skill to Equip. It gives bonuses to Attack power which boosts melee damage, Armor which will lessen melee Damage and Stamina which passivly raises your total Hit Points and allows you to do more damage via styles. Shields give the added effect of randomly lessening melee damage you recieve, the amount removed is between 1 and the total DPR the weapon has.

legendary-tower-shield.name: Legendary tower shield
legendary-tower-shield.desc: A Legendary Shield, It Requires the TWO-HANDED SHIELD skill to Equip. It gives bonuses to Attack power which boosts melee damage, Armor which will lessen melee Damage and Dexterity which improves your chances to dodge melee attacks. Shields give the added effect of randomly lessening melee damage you recieve, the amount removed is between 1 and the total DPR the weapon has.

work-gloves.name: Work gloves
work-gloves.desc: Thick cloth gloves to keep your hands callous-free.  They can be equipped via the Inventory > Equipment screen if you are of the Crafter profession.

work-pants.name: Work pants
work-pants.desc: Heavy canvas trousers with tons of pockets and tool loops.  Can be equipped via the Inventory > Equipment screen if you are of the Crafter profession.

work-shirt.name: Work shirt
work-shirt.desc: A sturdy canvas shirt with plenty of pockets for holding tools.  It can be equipped via the Inventory > Equipment screen if you are of the Crafter profession.

work-boots.name: Work boots
work-boots.desc: Sturdy canvas boots with wooden soles, treated so that mud and other ickiness slide right off.  Can be equipped via the Inventory > Equipment screen if you are of the Crafter profession.

work-hat.name: Work hat
work-hat.desc: A wide-brimmed hat for keeping off sun, sawdust, and other junk. Can be equipped via the Inventory > Equipment screen if you are of the Crafter Profession.

work-toolbelt.name: Work toolbelt
work-toolbelt.desc: A wide, strong belt with plenty of clips and loops for tools.  Can be equipped via the Inventory > Equipment screen if you are of the Apprentice profession.

barrel.name: barrel
barrel.desc: A barrel full of sharp bits.  Can be equipped to the Ammo slot via the Inventory > Equipment screen.  Used as Ammo for Catapults.

siege-cannon.name: siege cannon
siege-cannon.desc: A rather devastating meld of long metal tube and wood, that tends to have a nice negative effect on the wall at which it is pointed.

battering-ram-head.name: battering ram head
battering-ram-head.desc: A roughly spherical attachment for your handy battering ram, useful for knocking on doors with confidence.  Can be equipped to the ammo slot via the Inventory > Equipment screen if you have the Siege Weapons skill.

balista-ammo.name: balista ammo
balista-ammo.desc: A huge arrow with a wickedly sharp tip.  Can be equipped to the ammo slot via the Inventory > Equipment screen if you have the Siege Weapon skill.

buckshot-cannon.name: buckshot cannon
buckshot-cannon.desc: A large metal cannon made for sieging Allegiance outposts. Equip this item via the Inventory > Equipment screen. You will also need the correct type of ammo equipped.

flaming-oil-barrel.name: flaming oil barrel
flaming-oil-barrel.desc: A barrel full of oil and set on fire.  Can be equipped to the Ammo slot via the Inventory > Equipment screen.  Used as Ammo for Catapults.

tongs.name: tongs
tongs.desc: Tongs are one of the items you can use to gather gems, they require the GEOLOGY skill to equip and when Equipped gives a bonus to the GEOLOGY skill. You do not need to equip it in order to gather gems.

gem-hammer.name: gem hammer
gem-hammer.desc: The Gem hammer is one of the items you can use to gather gems, it Requires the GEOLOGY skill to equip and when Equipped gives a bonus to the GEOLOGY skill. You do not need to equip it in order to gather gems.

league-bandana.name: League Bandana
league-bandana.desc: This item signifies your loyalty to the Pirate League.

navy-badge.name: Navy badge
navy-badge.desc: This item signifies your committment to the Myzan Navy.

mercenary-brand.name: Mercenary Brand
mercenary-brand.desc: This item is a gift given to all Mercenaries by the Gods.
